WEBVTT


00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.040
The top three countries in the world with

00:00:02.040 --> 00:00:03.600
the best healthcare systems

00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:04.840
No. 3 Germany.

00:00:04.840 --> 00:00:07.080
Covering 100% of the population,

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:11.000
Germany allocates about 11.7% of its GDP to healthcare.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.840
The German system is known for its short waiting times,

00:00:13.840 --> 00:00:16.000
access to the latest medical technologies

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.800
and a high density of doctors,

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:21.440
with approximately 4.3 physicians per 1,000 residents.

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:22.920
No. 2 Switzerland

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:24.800
Switzerland consistently ranks among

00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:26.200
the top countries in healthcare

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.280
due to its universal health coverage system

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:31.120
where 99% of the population is insured.

00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:33.400
Switzerland boasts high quality medical services

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:34.760
in advanced technology.

00:00:34.760 --> 00:00:37.680
Its healthcare expenditure is around 12% of GDP.

00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:39.240
Before revealing the number one,

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:41.560
remember to subscribe and like the video!

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:42.960
Number one Japan.

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:45.120
Japan has the highest health score in the world

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.560
with a life expectancy of 85 years.

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:49.760
Japan's healthcare system is based on mandatory

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:51.000
social health insurance,

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:53.280
which covers almost all medical services.

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:54.320
The government regulates

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:56.440
the fees and quality of healthcare providers,

00:00:56.440 --> 00:00:58.960
ensuring equal access for all. And you,

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:01.080
do you have a good healthcare system where you're at?

00:01:01.080 --> 00:01:02.356
Let me know in the comments.
